  rdfs:comment           "ES: To  determine  whether  RIC-19  is  a  direct  effector  of  RAB-2, we coexpressed RIC-19 with either wild-type or GTP-restricted (DA) or GDP-bound constitutively inactive (DN) HA-tagged  RAB-2  forms  in  HeLa  cells  and  immunoprecipitated RAB-2 using anti-HA antibodies. RIC-19 could be specifically affinity  purified  with  RAB-2(Q65L)DA  and  to  a  lesser  extent with  wild-type  RAB-2  (Fig.  10A)  but  not  with  the  inactive form RAB-2(S20N)DN, suggesting that RIC-19 is indeed an \neffector of RAB-2." , "Automated change 2023-03-16: RO:0002406 replaced by RO:0002629" ;
  lego:evidence          :5716c41300000687 ;
